benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogs - Retrieve audit logs by account id

covered: Valid Request: GET retrieves audit logs for an existing account returning 200 with AuditLog objects
Empty Response: When an account has no audit logs, returns 200 with an empty JSON array
Query Parameters: Extra query parameters are provided but ignored and do not affect results
Authorization: Tests cover missing and invalid authentication tokens resulting in 401 Unauthorized
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets (page size, page tokens, and navigating pages)
Rate Limiting: No tests verify behavior under high request throughput or throttling (e.g., 429 or 503 on bursts)
Caching Behavior: No tests validate caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or conditional requests
Authorization edge-case: No test explicitly covers 403 Forbidden or insufficient privileges scenarios
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (e.g., page and pageSize) to ensure correct paging behavior for large audit log sets
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to validate proper handling under high load (expect 429/503 as appropriate)
Add caching header tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and conditional requests (If-None-Match) to verify caching behavior
Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient privileges in authorization scenarios
Enhance negative testing with additional invalid query parameter combinations and edge-case accountId formats
